-- Saudi Aramco Sees Potential for Wind, Geothermal Energy in West
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-02-20T14:49:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-20/saudi-aramco-sees-potential-for-wind-geothermal-energy-in-west.html
Saudi Arabian Oil Co. sees potential
to use wind and geothermal energy in the western parts of the
Kingdom to produce electricity, a company’s official said.  There is “technical” potential to produce 25,000
megawatts of electricity from wind, Faisal Habiballah, head of
solar team at the company, known as  Saudi Aramco , told delegates
today at a renewable energy conference in Dhahran,  Saudi Arabia .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar, Saudi Arabia at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  on   sev@bloomberg.net . 